    body_en:
      "**Newsletter cron auth rolled back.** `cron-newsletter-daily-background` no longer requires `CRON_SECRET` on the trigger URL â the daily Resend send is back to the same URL-obscurity convention as the other Netlify background crons. If cron-job.org was updated with `?secret=âĶ` after v2.6.12's short-lived guard, remove that query param so the nightly tick can fire again without an `Unauthorized` early return. `SPEC.md` and `.env.example` are aligned with the previous contract.\n\n**Home Top 24h ÂŦ Read / Lue Âŧ checkbox.** `<Top24hHero>` accepts optional `isRead` + `onToggleRead`; `<HomeTop24hHero>` forwards them from `<BriefingPage>`. A compact bottom-left checkbox marks today's briefing as read; the choice is stored in the `top24hRead` cookie keyed to today's UTC date so yesterday's state does not carry over. When checked, the hero is demoted below ÂŦ All transcribed videos Âŧ instead of crowding the top of the home â unchecking restores the top placement on the next render. New i18n string `top24hHeroReadLabel`.\n\n**Responsive chrome on the Top 24h hero + transcribed-videos list.** `globals.css` adds layout classes for the hero header (title, master expand/collapse, generated-at line) and for the home ÂŦ All transcribed videos Âŧ panel (list rows, topic chip, date, score column, pager). Mobile breakpoints tighten typography and spacing without changing the desktop register.\n\n**Favorites: video rows open in-app when a transcript page exists.** `GET /api/user/favorites` resolves each YouTube favorite to an internal `/{topic}/v/{date}/{slug}` path via new `getVideoPagePathsByVideoIds()` in `src/lib/supabase/videos.ts` (preferred UI lang, first match wins). `<FavoritesPage>` uses `<Link>` for video titles when `internalPath` is present and keeps external tabs for article URLs; YouTube URLs are treated as video favorites even when legacy rows stored `source_type: article`.\n\n**SSR video pages: favorite control + richer timestamp.** `/{topic}/v/{date}/{slug}` embeds `<VideoPageFavoriteButton>` beside the published-at line (hour + minute in the visitor locale) so logged-in users can bookmark from the SEO surface. `VideosPage` appends the visible day count to ÂŦ Videos of the day Âŧ once the list has loaded.\n\n**Release.** Bump 2.6.14 â 2.6.15. No DB migration.",
